forge
------------------------------------------
An OpenGL interop library that can be used with ArrayFire or any other
application using CUDA or OpenCL compute backend. The goal of Forge is to
provide high performance OpenGL visualizations for C/C++ applications that use
CUDA/OpenCL. Forge uses OpenGL >=3.3 forward compatible contexts, so please
make sure you have capable hardware before trying it out.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libGL1-19.1.6-1
  libfontconfig1-2.13.1-2
  libforge1-1.0.8-1bl1
  libfreetype6-2.10.4-2
  libgcc1-11.2.0-1
  libglfw3-3.3.4-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.2.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.2.0-1
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.13.1-2
  libfreetype-devel-2.10.4-2
  libglfw-devel-3.3.4-1bl1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/arrayfire/forge

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/arrayfire/forge/archive/v1.0.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack forge-1.0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./forge-1.0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/forge-1.0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/forge-1.0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libforge1-1.0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libforge-devel-1.0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

